node.text: Lucia and Agustin of @proyectopasillodeco's home used to belong to Lucia's grandparents and looked nothing like it does today. The pair made the space much brighter by getting rid of the dark, old wallpaper, and then got to work transforming each room one DIY at a time. They did such a great job, it's no wonder they were crowned our 2021 Small/Cool contest winners! 👑

node.text:
It took 20 (!) gallons of paint and a few DIYs to totally transform this old wallpapered Philly house. “I’ve really been inspired by the history of the house. According to historic maps, it was built sometime in the 1870s, and at one point it was even a boarding house! The trim, the floors, the beautiful architecture — most of the last year has just been stripping things away to let the house just be,” says Katie of @row_sweet_home. Swipe for the living room’s “before” and see the whole home transformation at the link in our bio. 

(Images & Home: @row_sweet_home)
